Wrap an I/O handle to GZIP compress/uncompress.

Example:
// generate GZIP CSV file
readAll(site).ioWriteCsv(ioGzip(`io/sites.gz`))

// read GZIP CSV file
ioGzip(`io/sites.gz`).ioReadCsv

Evaluate a relationship query and return the named constraints
as a dict.  The query slot names are the dict names and the matching
record dicts are the dict values. Missing matches are silently ignored
and ambiguous matches return an indeterminate record.

Example:
// spec
MyAhu: Equip {
points: {
dat: DischargeAirTempSensor
rat: DischargeAirTempSensor
}
}

// axon
myAhuPoints: read(ahu).queryNamed(spec("mylib::MyAhu.points"))

// result
{
dat: {dis:"DAT", discharge, air, temp, sensor, ...},
rat: {dis:"RAT", return, air, temp, sensor, ...}
}

Convenience for converting a grid to valid JSON for web api calls, e.g.
data: {personalizations:
[{
  to: [{email: "mmelillo@albireoenergy.com"}]}],
  from: {email: "mmelillo@albireoenergy.com"},
  subject: "Sending with SendGrid is Fun",
  content: [{type: "text/plain", value: "and easy to do anywhere, even with fantom!"}
]}
data.toHttpJson().callRestApi(..)

Query local sparks along three dimensions of target x dates x rules.
Targets and rules are any expr accepted by `toRecList` or null for all.
Span is any expr accepted by `toSpan`.

Examples:
  // read sparks last month for all targets and all rules
  ruleSparks(null, lastMonth, null)

  // read sparks only where targetRef is a given equip
  read(rtu).ruleSparks(lastMonth, null)

  // read sparks for all targets for a given rule
  ruleSparks(null, lastMonth, rule)

Get the spec's declared children slots as dict of Specs.

Examples:
specSlots(Ahu)  >>  {ahu: Spec}

Find a top-level function by name or by reference and return its tags.
If not found throw exception or return null based on checked flag.

Example:
func("readAll")
func(readAll)

Parse Axon source code into an abstract syntax tree modeled as a
tree of dicts.  Each node has a 'type' tag which specified the node type.
Common AST shapes:

123    =>  {type:"literal", val:123}
a      =>  {type:"var", name:"a"}
not a  =>  {type:"not", operand:{type:"var", name:"a"}}
a + b  =>  {type:"add", lhs:{type:"var", name:"a"}, rhs:{type:"var", name:"b"}}

NOTE: the keys and structure of the AST is subject to change over time.

Get the effective children slots as a dict of Specs.

Examples:
specSlots(Ahu)  >>  {equip: Spec, points: Spec, ahu: Spec}
